bug.short_desc: [abrt] lxqt-panel: QSocketNotifier::setEnabled(): lxqt-panel killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Version-Release number of selected component: lxqt-panel-0.11.0-2.fc25
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.8.0 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: lxqt-panel crash_function: QSocketNotifier::setEnabled executable: /usr/bin/lxqt-panel global_pid: 1364 kernel: 4.8.0-0.rc7.git0.1.fc25.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 4089 D8F2 FDB1 9C98 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (10 frames) #0 QSocketNotifier::setEnabled at kernel/qsocketnotifier.cpp:246 #1 QSocketNotifier::~QSocketNotifier at kernel/qsocketnotifier.cpp:164 #3 QScopedPointerDeleter<QSocketNotifier>::cleanup at /usr/include/qt5/QtCore/qscopedpointer.h:60 #4 QScopedPointer<QSocketNotifier, QScopedPointerDeleter<QSocketNotifier> >::~QScopedPointer at /usr/include/qt5/QtCore/qscopedpointer.h:107 #5 (anonymous namespace)::SignalHandler::~SignalHandler at /usr/src/debug/liblxqt-0.11.0/lxqtapplication.cpp:170 #6 QScopedPointerDeleter<(anonymous namespace)::SignalHandler>::cleanup at /usr/include/qt5/QtCore/qscopedpointer.h:60 #7 QScopedPointer<(anonymous namespace)::SignalHandler, QScopedPointerDeleter<(anonymous namespace)::SignalHandler> >::~QScopedPointer at /usr/include/qt5/QtCore/qscopedpointer.h:107 #8 __cxa_finalize at cxa_finalize.c:56 #9 __do_global_dtors_aux #10 ??
Obviously something in liblxqt, as backtrace tells. Unfortunately, there's no source file (and line #) given where the crash happens.
*** Bug 1381913 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
